some_columns","submitter_user":{"username":"sjamaan","created_at":"2018-08-30T05:08:17.000-05:00","is_admin":false,"about":"Scheme enthusiast from the Netherlands. Core maintainer of CHICKEN Scheme. Check out [my blog](https://www.more-magic.net/) for more information.","is_moderator":false,"karma":3499,"avatar_url":"/avatars/sjamaan-100.png","invited_by_user":"evhan"},"tags":["databases"]},{"short_id":"5n47qf","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/5n47qf","created_at":"2022-02-21T15:37:16.000-06:00","title":"Ways to break into computer science research without a formal education or degree?","url":"","score":11,"flags":0,"comment_count":8,"description":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAs a basis for discussion:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDoes anyone know stories of people without degrees or PHD‚Äôs doing strong research work in their respective fields (submitting co-authoring papers etc)?\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eIf so, what their journey was like?\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWhat other companies / organizations have research teams beside Amazon, MSFT, Google?\u2028\u2028\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSome experience of breaking into ‚Äúresearchy‚Äù roles \u0026amp; teams:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eNote all these folks below that I‚Äôve observed have habits of reading research papers, RFC‚Äôs (perhaps expected), they‚Äôre pretty phenomenal engineers \u0026amp; people\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eFriend at Microsoft Research\u003c/strong\u003e works alongside researchers, they build tools that bring the researchers tools to life; they have to have a solid grasp of the tech side to a certain degree\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eFriend alongside a team full of CS/Physics PHDs\u003c/strong\u003e; they spoke at a quantum conference recently\u2028 \u0026amp; they do some research;  bootcamp grad, dropout\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eFriend works on database internals / distributed systems, has worked alongside creators of core tech\u003c/strong\u003e, has presented at conferences, written very strong technical content for his company‚Äôs engineering blog (FAANG+ company)\u2028\u2028; bootcamp grad, no tech degree\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u2028From the outside, breaking into research doesn‚Äôt seem impossible, BUT it seems there are some factors that can increase your opportunity:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDoes the current organization have research opportunities/teams?\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eJoining the right team/timing; maybe who you know?\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBreaking in from the inside ‚Äì years at the company, /social capital, reputation internally?\u2028\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/5n47qf/ways_break_into_computer_science","submitter_user":{"username":"cliffordfajardo","created_at":"2020-12-23T17:40:47.000-06:00","is_admin":false,"about":"Software Engineer at LinkedIn. \r\nInterests: Open Source Research \u0026 Software, Developer tooling, BASBüß†, Education, Communities","is_moderator":false,"karma":30,"avatar_url":"/avatars/cliffordfajardo-100.png","invited_by_user":"chriskrycho","github_username":"cliffordfajardo","twitter_username":"cliffordfajard0"},"tags":["ask","compsci","education"]},{"short_id":"zfgqin","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/zfgqin","created_at":"2022-02-22T07:33:25.000-06:00","title":"Linux's getrandom() Sees A 8450% Performance Improvement With Latest Code","url":"https://www.phoronix.com/scan.php?page=news_item\u0026px=Linux-getrandom-8450p","score":2,"flags":0,"comment_count":1,"description":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/zfgqin/linux_s_getrandom_sees_8450_performance","submitter_user":{"username":"atoponce","created_at":"2018-05-27T14:17:15.000-05:00","is_admin":false,"about":"Security researcher, amateur cryptographer, password en